text = "The story of the game:
Project Unknown is a game about re-creating life from virtually nothing.
Awaking in a bunker, the player knows nothing.
There is nothing inside the bunker except a letter, more on the later. 
Since there is nothing inside the bunker, the player leaves the bunker to explore the outside world. 
Exiting the bunker reveals a wasteland extending for miles. 
Existing in the outside world comes with at a cost. 
Prolonged exposer outside causes infection. 
Returning to the bunker, the player reads the letter. 
The letter explains a tiny bit of lore and teaches the player how to gather resources and craft a basic crafting bench. 
The letter also explains to the player a tiny bit about the infection. 
Eventually you learn that you can survival outside, but the time is very limited as you do not want to become infected. 
You gather resources and eventually are able to expand your bunker(Bunker Upgrading). 
Learning new recipes and the world around you, you are eventually able to create a Protective Suit. 
This suit allows you to exist in the waste land for longer. With this you are able to explore more. 
This leads to the player finding abandoned labs as well as other TBD(To Be Determined) structures. 
In these structures you find new, much harder, recipes. 
You also find Lore Items which help you figure out what happened. Exploring enough structures will get you the ultimate recipe. 
The Creation Recipe. 
This is the way to \"beat\" the game. It tells the player how to re-create life."
label_settings = SubResource("LabelSettings_mb34y")

